1
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:23,080
What are you doing, Dad?

2
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:30,640
Cent!

3
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:33,840
Every Facebook page is posting about you.

4
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,800
-It's trending on Twitter too!
-Really?

5
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:38,240
#NoGoodbye.

6
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:39,960
Thank you for the compliment.

7
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,280
I mean, for saying
my drawing is beautiful.

8
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:46,880
Thank you. Thank you so much!

9
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:48,560
You're working on the app
in exchange for shares.

10
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:52,760
And you'll help with her project
as my son.

11
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:56,600
-Mom!
-Hey, listen!

12
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,840
Thank you, my dear son.

13
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:06,400
-If we push a little longer, we won't--
-Stop it!

14
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:11,120
I don't have time to listen
to this nonsense of yours.

15
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:14,800
The business world isn't as easy
as you're making it sound.

16
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:19,440
And I've never once told you
that I'd let you work at the factory.

17
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,360
Go find a job like your sister did.

18
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:29,040
I'm also going to cancel
all your credit cards.

19
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:36,720
You've graduated. Take responsibility.
Earn your own money, see how hard it is.

20
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:41,720
From now on, I won't help you
with anything anymore.

21
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:50,320
Mom.

22
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:53,680
What's wrong with Dad?

23
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:57,840
Why is he yelling at me,
pressuring me like this?

24
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,840
I haven't gotten a job yet

25
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:04,760
because I was waiting for him
to call me to help at the factory.

26
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,520
I'm not just sitting around wasting money.

27
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:13,560
I've got so many project ideas,
but he never listens to me!

28
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:20,760
What's really going on
at the factory, Mom?

29
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:24,000
I don't know.

30
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:30,440
I really don't know, dear.
Just do what your dad says, okay?

31
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,960
That's all I know.

32
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:39,240
Pung! Pung, stop!

33
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:41,600
Hey, Pung!

34
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,920
Hey, stop!

35
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,520
Hey! Why are you blocking my car?

36
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:49,400
Did something happen at home?

37
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:52,560
Nobody's hurt. If anything, it's me!

38
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,440
Do you know what's wrong with Dad?

39
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:58,840
Just now, he suddenly yelled at me,
said I'm wasting money.

40
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:01,440
He told me to go get a job like you.

41
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:05,720
I'm so confused why he won't
let me work at the factory.

42
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,840
Do you know what's going on with Dad?

43
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:13,880
I don't know. He never
tells anyone what he's thinking.

44
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:18,880
I don't want to work for our family
anyway, so it doesn't affect me.

45
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:23,080
If Dad won't let you work there,
then don't.

46
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,320
Go find another job.

47
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:28,680
Hey! To be honest,

48
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:33,040
I think Dad is right.
You should cut down on spending.

49
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:35,800
Every time you shop, I almost pass out!

50
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:37,920
Geez.

51
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,120
See? That face again.

52
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:44,840
You spend money like our family prints it.
If you don't want me nagging you,

53
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,400
just save some money.

54
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,520
I'm off to work. See you tonight.

55
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,320
Hey, wait!

56
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,760
Can you talk to Dad for me?

57
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:59,320
Ask him what's going on.

58
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:03,880
Does he not trust
that I can actually work at the factory?

59
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:12,560
Asking won't help. Dad only speaks
when he wants to. That's it, Pound.

60
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,840
Alright, I'm off to work.

61
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,000
You're going to Japan tomorrow?

62
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:34,920
Just for two days. I'm going
to talk to Ken about the shares.

63
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,520
He wants to sell them,
but he's too hesitant to sell to me.

64
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:41,800
He feels bad selling it at a high price,
so I want to meet him and clear things up.

65
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:44,440
Cent.

66
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:50,120
I know you love this company
and you love your work.

67
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,560
Don't worry about my shares.

68
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:57,800
If you can do the job I asked for,

69
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,440
I'll transfer you the shares.

70
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,400
Mom.

71
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,600
I'll ask you straight.

72
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:09,400
Why are those things so important to you?

73
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:13,280
It doesn't make any sense.

74
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:16,880
It should be the government's
responsibility, not ours.

75
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:21,960
When you're my age…

76
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:29,480
When you start getting closer to death
with every breath, you'll understand

77
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:34,200
that doing something good for others

78
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:37,200
is a kind of happiness money can't buy.

79
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:42,880
And the reason I made you come help me

80
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:46,960
is because I want you to experience
this kind of happiness early on.

81
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:52,400
Maybe you'll understand
and spend your time helping others.

82
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:58,360
This sounds like a superhero mission, Mom.

83
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:00,560
Yes.

84
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:05,120
You're my superhero.

85
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,480
Wait, Mom.

86
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:12,560
I'm just a normal guy. I work for money.

87
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:15,200
Now I'm even working
to earn shares from my own mother.

88
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:19,880
But don't worry, I'm giving it my all.

89
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:24,160
As for this save-the-world mission,
it's a bit too far for me.

90
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:26,960
Right now, I'd rather focus
on saving my own company.

91
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,640
Alright?

92
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,720
I'm off.

93
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,320
Mr. Cent.

94
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:55,720
Your mom told me to bring you a suitcase.

95
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:59,240
It's brand new. Which size do you want
for your trip to Japan?

96
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:02,000
One bag is enough.

97
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:03,000
Huh?

98
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:06,760
If you didn't say anything,
I'd think you were just going to Khao Yai.

99
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:11,320
By the way, you said
you're only going for two days, right?

100
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:14,400
When you come back, you'll start working
for your mom right away, right?

101
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:15,520
Yes.

102
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,480
-Okay.
-Wait.

103
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,080
Why'd you suddenly ask about my work?

104
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,440
What's going on?

105
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:26,400
Nothing!

106
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:29,360
Tell me, Pong!

107
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:33,520
-Nothing at all.
-Pong!

108
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:38,480
SOM TAM PALACE

109
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:47,720
I just wanted you to know, your mom

110
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,160
really loves you, Cent.

111
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:52,160
She thinks about you all the time.

112
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:55,320
Lately, she keeps saying
she wants you to come live with her.

113
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,480
I know!

114
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,840
But I have to work.

115
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:03,400
I work this hard
because I want her to be comfortable.

116
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:06,520
Your mom is already comfortable, though.

117
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,640
Maybe you could work a little less.

118
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,880
Or even better,

119
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:15,840
get a girlfriend and have kids.
She wouldn't feel lonely then.

120
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:20,080
I understand, though.
Girlfriends are hard to find.

121
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:22,520
Should I help you find one?

122
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:25,120
I know lots of nice girls.

123
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,640
By the way, what kind of girl do you like?

124
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:38,240
FULLY THOUGHT-OUT CONCEPT

125
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,160
SOLID STORY

126
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,120
NO VIOLENCE, EASY TO REMEMBER
A CLEAR, UNIQUE DNA

127
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:50,640
Hey!

128
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:53,120
I've got a meeting with an agency.
Come with me!

129
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,840
What agency?

130
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:56,600
An advertising agency!

131
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:59,000
They contacted me
to review artificial tears.

132
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:01,800
They called me in for a briefing
at their company before noon today.

133
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:03,600
-Today?
-Yes, today!

134
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,320
Congrats, girl!

135
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,160
So you're coming with me, okay?

136
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:09,440
Come with me!

137
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:12,840
Please! I'm really excited!

138
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:17,360
I'm so happy! Come with me, okay?

139
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,480
-Hello.
-Hello.

140
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,480
Hello.

141
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:41,280
You look even prettier in person
than in your videos.

142
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,040
Thank you.

143
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:46,840
So what exactly is the brief?

144
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:49,680
What do I need to do?

145
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,600
To be honest,

146
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:56,320
if it's not a product I already use,

147
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:58,520
I wouldn't have accepted it.

148
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:02,960
I actually got other offers too,

149
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:05,840
but I turned them down
because I don't use those products.

150
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:08,200
Wow, so you really use it?

151
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:12,760
The client will be so happy to hear that.
They specifically requested you.

152
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:17,840
So what do I need to do?

153
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:20,880
It's a still photo campaign
for Instagram and fan page posts.

154
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:25,680
The product is artificial tears.
The mood and tone is blue.

155
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:27,840
The key message is clean,

156
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:29,680
safe, and trustworthy.

157
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:32,800
How high-res do the photos need to be?

158
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:35,880
You can use your phone as normal.

159
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:37,480
Send the photos for us to choose from,

160
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:40,960
the ones you like, along with captions.

161
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,640
We'll post them within seven days.

162
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:44,480
Post…

163
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,720
Within seven days, okay.

164
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:49,040
-Got it.
-And about the payment…

165
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:50,280
It's okay!

166
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:52,360
Like I said,

167
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:55,440
if it's not a product I already use,
I wouldn't take it anyway.

168
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:57,560
So let's just go

169
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:59,440
with whatever the client offers.
That's fine.

170
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:01,720
You're so lovely.

171
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,360
Bring it here.

172
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,440
Then let's go through the contract.

173
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:08,520
-Okay.
-Alright.

174
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:12,320
You can read it carefully.
If you have any questions, just ask me.

175
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:15,040
And if everything's fine, sign here.

176
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:16,600
Okay.

177
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:23,960
You've had other review offers?
You never told me.

178
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:27,760
I didn't tell you
because there aren't any.

179
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:34,200
-Then why would you say that to her?
-Hey, keep it down.

180
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:38,360
I need to boost my image a little.

181
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:42,040
Good thing she didn't ask
what brands contacted me.

182
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:44,680
If she asked,
I wouldn't even know what to say.

183
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:49,480
So this artificial tears brand,
you actually use it?

184
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:52,840
I just bought it
when I went to pick you up.

185
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:54,840
Franc!

186
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:58,440
It's just something I saw influencers do

187
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:01,600
in reviews, making it seem
like they actually use it.

188
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:05,560
So I tried it. Turns out it works.

189
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:08,840
You're crazy. If you're so prepared,
why did you drag me along?

190
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:13,840
If I came alone,
it would look too confident.

191
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:15,760
Bringing a friend along just feels nicer.

192
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:20,840
After this, you're free, right?
Help me shoot the content.

193
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:24,320
I'm doing it today.
I'll also call Yuan to help.

194
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:26,480
-Hey, but I've--
-Please.

195
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:33,320
Yuan, what time do you finish work today?

196
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:36,240
Come help me shoot something.

197
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:39,320
You take the best photos of me.

198
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:42,600
It's my first project,
so it has to be your work, right?

199
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,040
Please!

200
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:47,600
It has to be you, okay?

201
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,400
Okay, see you!

202
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:54,080
If you don't want a regular job,

203
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:56,840
what are you going to do then?

204
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:01,440
I'll probably invest in something.

205
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:05,400
You mean that vacation house
you said you'd rent out?

206
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:09,760
That won't work anymore.
Dad said he's going to sell it.

207
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:14,320
Yeah. Dad won't let me work
at the factory.

208
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:17,080
I'll have to start my own business.

209
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:20,680
But I still have no idea
what I'm going to do.

210
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:26,440
Are we…

211
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:30,240
stepping into the real world
after graduation?

212
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:33,760
A world that's nothing
like what we used to dream about.

213
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,560
Yeah!

214
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:39,240
I was so sure
I'd help with the family business,

215
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:40,840
but suddenly, I just can't.

216
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:44,160
As for me,

217
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:48,600
the teacher recruitment exam results
are out too.

218
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,320
-How did it go?
-Did you pass?

219
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,320
I'm too scared to check.

220
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:57,920
Huh?

221
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:03,360
I'll go back to the office first
and check later.

222
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:06,920
If I find out,

223
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:09,920
my life might change too.

224
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:14,960
Maybe what we dreamed of and reality

225
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:18,080
aren't the same at all.

226
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:56,840
LIST OF SUCCESSFUL CANDIDATES
FOR ASSISTANT TEACHER RECRUITMENT

227
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:18,800
<i>So we do it like this.</i>

228
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:21,200
-And then, sift like this!
-Do it like this.

229
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:25,160
-That's right. Can you do it?
-You're doing great.

230
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:27,800
-That's right.
-<i>Have you ever taken a baking class?</i>

231
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:31,960
<i>Not formally. My mom taught me.</i>

232
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:34,000
Do you like it sweet?

233
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:36,000
You like it sweet? Okay!

234
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:43,960
Would you be interested
in becoming a full-time assistant teacher?

235
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:46,280
I'm actually looking for someone.

236
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:50,880
Thank you so much.

237
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:54,640
But I applied
for the teacher recruitment exam.

238
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:58,480
If I pass, I'll have to quit.
So I feel a bit bad about it.

239
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:01,400
That's a shame.
But if you change your mind, let me know.

240
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:04,040
<i>Do you think my cakes are really good?</i>

241
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:06,400
Are they good enough

242
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:09,599
for you to actually pay for them?

243
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:11,720
Good food is good food.

244
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:14,480
It doesn't matter who made it.

245
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:17,599
Bonus, have more confidence in yourself.

246
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:20,160
Okay?

247
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:35,800
The teacher recruitment results are out.
Did you check it yet?

248
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:40,120
Bonus, how did it go? Did you pass?

249
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:53,200
That face means you didn't pass, right?

250
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:01,800
I'm sorry, Dad.

251
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:04,080
I'm sorry, Mom.

252
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:08,880
I know you were really hoping for this.

253
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:13,680
I'm sorry for disappointing you.

254
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:19,080
It's okay, dear. If you didn't pass,
you can always try again.

255
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,680
Dad. Mom.

256
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:30,280
If I don't become a teacher…

257
00:18:34,320 --> 00:18:37,160
If I do something else
that's not teaching,

258
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:40,800
would you be mad at me?

259
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:44,760
What kind of other career
are you talking about?

260
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:50,680
I want to sell desserts.

261
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:53,920
Desserts?

262
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:57,280
Like the ones
we make at home and give away?

263
00:18:57,360 --> 00:19:01,960
Or like the ones I make to sell at school?

264
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:06,320
That won't make much profit,
and it's tiring.

265
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:09,800
Making each batch of desserts
takes so much time.

266
00:19:09,880 --> 00:19:11,240
It takes up the whole day.

267
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:14,640
I think you should just drop this idea.

268
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,520
But Dad, I'm willing to work hard.

269
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:24,080
I believe if I really
put my heart into it,

270
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:27,400
I can do it better than being a teacher.

271
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,600
Hold on.

272
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:39,080
Are you giving up
just because you failed once?

273
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:41,560
I'm not giving up, Dad.

274
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:44,280
I've thought this through.

275
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:48,600
When I make desserts, I feel happy.

276
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:52,600
It's fun. It doesn't even feel tiring.

277
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:55,400
And I want to keep doing it.

278
00:19:58,040 --> 00:20:01,880
I want to give it my all.
I want to try my hardest

279
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:06,600
before I grow old and die
without ever trying anything.

280
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:13,680
How about this?

281
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:19,240
You can be a teacher
and make desserts, like I used to.

282
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:25,200
I don't want to do things halfway.

283
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:29,520
If I'm going to start a dessert business,

284
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:32,480
I want to focus on just that.

285
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:37,720
It's better than wasting time
on something I know isn't right for me.

286
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:44,040
To run a business, you need knowledge.

287
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:46,240
It's not enough to like it or love it.

288
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:51,680
You need capital to start a business.
Do you have any?

289
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:53,760
We're civil servants.

290
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:56,240
Business isn't for us.

291
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:59,000
It'll only end in failure.

292
00:21:09,520 --> 00:21:12,120
Why don't you learn more
and do some research

293
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:14,120
before you jump in, dear?

294
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:18,000
If things go wrong,
it won't hurt you too badly. Okay?

295
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:27,080
Raise your hands, both of them.

296
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:30,520
-Like this?
-Look over here.

297
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:34,200
Try tilting your face
slightly to the right.

298
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:36,920
Make your eyes look a bit nostalgic.

299
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:40,320
A little sad, but not too gloomy.

300
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:43,080
-Okay, try it.
-Sad but not gloomy?

301
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:44,520
How do I even do that? Show me!

302
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:47,760
I have no idea either.

303
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:53,320
-Alright, I'll give it a try.
-Go on.

304
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:55,600
Look to my right. Look away a bit.

305
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:57,440
Hey, if there's a shot you like,

306
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:59,840
put it on the drive.
I'll download and edit it.

307
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,240
Got it.

308
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:03,400
Okay.

309
00:22:04,560 --> 00:22:06,280
Okay. Beautiful.

310
00:22:33,360 --> 00:22:34,560
That's enough.

311
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:36,720
Alright.

312
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:42,800
Okay.

313
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:45,200
Yeah, this is good.

314
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,720
Hey!

315
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:54,960
Get me a towel, Fuang!

316
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:57,520
-Here.
-I'm fine!

317
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,600
-Are you wet?
-Check the phone!

318
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:02,880
Look at the photos!

319
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:04,720
Okay, all the photos are still here.

320
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,000
Thank goodness!

321
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:08,760
I would've been so mad if we lost them.

322
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:12,880
You're soaked, and you're still worried
about the photos!

323
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:17,200
-How is it?
-This one's good!

324
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:18,280
Let me see.

325
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:20,280
-Good?
-This one's really good.

326
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:21,680
Yeah.

327
00:23:21,760 --> 00:23:26,160
-It's actually pretty good.
-Very artsy.

328
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:29,800
Right now, we've got two sets of photos,
one with lighting, one with ice.

329
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:33,080
I'll just add some cute little doodles
to give it more gimmick.

330
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:35,880
This is so cool. So cute!

331
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:37,760
-You like it?
-It's amazing!

332
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:39,120
I'm sure they'll love it.

333
00:23:39,640 --> 00:23:40,720
I like it too. Looks great.

334
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:43,840
-I'll send it over then.
-Okay.

335
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:49,920
Got it!

336
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,800
I'll send the photos and captions
to them now.

337
00:23:58,880 --> 00:23:59,920
Done!

338
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:03,760
Hey, but honestly, it's really easy.

339
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:06,440
I can teach you to do it yourself.
It's not hard. Want me to?

340
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:07,840
No need.

341
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:10,440
It's easier if you just do it for me.
Please?

342
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:11,920
-Whoa!
-Please!

343
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,440
Alright then.

344
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:18,320
I'll teach Yuan instead, in case I'm busy.
He'll be happy to help you.

345
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:19,240
Is that okay?

346
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:25,800
Sure. No problem. I can do it.

347
00:24:26,400 --> 00:24:28,040
Thanks, bestie!

348
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:34,960
-She replied!
-Whoa!

349
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:37,200
What did she say?

350
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:41,640
She said

351
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:44,440
the photos look great.
She'll send them to the client right away.

352
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:46,320
She'll update me if there's any feedback.

353
00:24:48,640 --> 00:24:49,760
What a relief!

354
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:53,920
Thanks so much, guys!

355
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:57,040
Come on, I'll treat you.
What do you want to eat?

356
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:59,920
Hey, I'll pass today. You guys go ahead.

357
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:03,720
I've got a meeting with Bonus.
She needs to discuss something with me.

358
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,840
What is it about?

359
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:09,680
I didn't pass the teacher exam.

360
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:13,560
But I'm not retaking it.

361
00:25:14,120 --> 00:25:16,000
I want to sell desserts.

362
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:17,600
-Huh?
-Huh?

363
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:20,200
I already told my parents,

364
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:22,960
but they don't really agree.

365
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:25,440
What do you guys think?

366
00:25:29,080 --> 00:25:31,480
I admit your desserts are really good.

367
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:35,200
But are you serious
about turning this into a full business?

368
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:38,640
What made you think of this?

369
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:44,000
When I make desserts, I'm happy.

370
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:47,680
I feel like I've been connected to it
since I was a kid.

371
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:52,520
I didn't do it much growing up,
but I can still do it easily.

372
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:54,360
Like it's always been inside me.

373
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:56,280
And when you make desserts,

374
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:00,320
you forget the outside world
and focus completely.

375
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:04,440
Your mind just stays
on what's in front of you.

376
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:08,000
You won't feel tired,

377
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:13,400
and you won't feel sleepy.
It's like you have energy.

378
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:17,520
It gives you the confidence to go for it.

379
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:19,800
Exactly!

380
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:23,600
I get it, because I feel the same way.

381
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:27,200
When was that?

382
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:30,840
When I designed clothes
for the kids next door

383
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:32,000
for their game competition.

384
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:36,120
I felt really happy doing it.

385
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:40,080
And my design even won a prize.

386
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:42,800
That's amazing!

387
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,240
Yeah! That's so cool, Yuan!

388
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:45,680
I got goosebumps!

389
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:51,920
I think, today I feel the same as Bonus.

390
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:57,640
I want to start my own clothing brand.

391
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:04,600
Wait! Don't get all emotional yet.

392
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:11,800
So Bonus realized she wants
to sell desserts, not be a teacher.

393
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:17,080
And Yuan wants
to start his own clothing brand.

394
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:22,640
You might know what you want to do.

395
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:25,280
But have you thought
about what to do next?

396
00:27:29,120 --> 00:27:30,240
-No idea.
-No idea.

397
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:41,920
I think you should try
talking to Fuang's boss.

398
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,160
Cent?

399
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:46,080
Fuang said he's smart, right?

400
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:48,520
He probably knows about business too.

401
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:51,720
He might be able to give you
some good advice.

402
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,920
If Peace were still around,

403
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:59,760
I would've told you to go talk to him,
but he's gone now.

404
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:05,440
The only friend of his
that you guys know is Cent, right?

405
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:13,120
But would he even agree to meet us?

406
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:14,880
Yeah.

407
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:23,600
I think he's actually pretty kind.

408
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:26,360
If it's just a few minutes of his time,

409
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:29,160
he should be down.

410
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:33,560
Why should I listen?
They're your friends, not mine.

411
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:39,200
Wait!

412
00:28:40,120 --> 00:28:42,000
I understand,

413
00:28:42,080 --> 00:28:45,040
but my friends
are really serious about this.

414
00:28:45,120 --> 00:28:48,920
Maybe you could give us
some good advice to guide us.

415
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:50,720
It would be a huge merit, you know.

416
00:28:51,520 --> 00:28:53,560
I already have enough merit.
I don't need more. Move!

417
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:07,360
But if you could spare some time
to meet my friends,

418
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:09,640
I'll work overtime!

419
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:10,960
You don't have to pay me extra.

420
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:14,240
You can make me work
on Saturdays, Sundays,

421
00:29:14,320 --> 00:29:17,560
mornings, afternoons, evenings, nights.
24/7 if you want.

422
00:29:17,640 --> 00:29:22,920
I'll do it all. Just please spare
a little time to meet my friends.

423
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:26,320
You'd go that far for your friends?

424
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:31,000
Yes. We've known each other for years
and grew up helping each other.

425
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:33,280
When I was struggling,
they were there for me too.

426
00:29:33,360 --> 00:29:36,040
Now I'm lucky to get advice from you.

427
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:38,960
-I want them to be as lucky as I was.
-Five minutes.

428
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:41,680
I'll listen for only five minutes.

429
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:44,760
Five minutes each!

430
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:47,360
Wait. How many people?

431
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:49,200
Just two!

432
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:52,840
Two people, five minutes each.
That's ten minutes.

433
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:55,640
Ten minutes in exchange for me
working my hardest for you,

434
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:57,640
-it's more than worth it.
-You said it.

435
00:29:58,160 --> 00:29:59,360
Don't forget your own words.

436
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,240
I won't!

437
00:30:01,320 --> 00:30:03,080
I'll work my hardest.

438
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:07,080
Thank you so much!

439
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:11,400
-Close the door for me too.
-Yes.

440
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:21,800
Have a safe trip and good luck! Bye!

441
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:50,480
-Hello.
-Hi.

442
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:52,680
Sorry, I'm here to submit an invoice.

443
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:55,800
-Please wait a moment.
-Yes.

444
00:31:06,080 --> 00:31:07,760
<i>These are the designs, sir.</i>

445
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:11,720
Eight designs? And you want them
done in two weeks?

446
00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:14,120
I can't make that deadline, Miss Tan.

447
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:17,040
The designs are quite difficult.

448
00:31:17,120 --> 00:31:18,520
And this fabric,

449
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:20,920
it drapes heavily and is hard to pleat.

450
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:22,560
I'll pay any price.

451
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:25,640
If you need to hire more people
or adjust the cost, just tell me.

452
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:28,640
It's not about the money, Miss Tan.

453
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:30,760
The work itself is too difficult.

454
00:31:30,840 --> 00:31:34,000
Even if you bring in more people,
it still won't be finished in time.

455
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:35,600
I know it's difficult,

456
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:40,240
but I really want this, sir.
Please help me. Please!

457
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:48,280
I think it's doable, Dad.

458
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:51,280
The pattern might be difficult.

459
00:31:51,880 --> 00:31:54,720
If the designer sets the fabric layout
and marks the key points,

460
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:56,600
it should speed things up.

461
00:31:57,640 --> 00:32:01,760
But even if it's faster, we probably
can't do eight designs in time.

462
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:04,800
Six designs is more realistic.

463
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:07,400
Who is that?

464
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:09,160
That's my son.

465
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:13,720
He usually has class at this time,
so you don't usually see him.

466
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:16,960
I was planning to have him help
at my brother's factory.

467
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:20,760
Alright then. Let's reduce it
to six designs.

468
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:24,680
As for the fabric layout,
I'll handle it myself so it goes faster.

469
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:28,720
-Thanks for the idea.
-Yes.

470
00:32:35,080 --> 00:32:36,560
Whoa! Thirty-five thousand baht?

471
00:32:46,440 --> 00:32:47,280
Yes?

472
00:32:47,360 --> 00:32:49,040
Yuan, where are you?

473
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:50,760
I've got good news for you.

474
00:32:50,840 --> 00:32:53,480
I'm helping Dad settle some invoices.
What's the good news?

475
00:32:53,560 --> 00:32:56,880
That shirt collar you suggested,
the client really liked it.

476
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:59,600
After adjusting the design,
it looks so much more premium.

477
00:32:59,680 --> 00:33:01,320
<i>Uncle is really happy.</i>

478
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:03,800
<i>So I want you to take over this project.</i>

479
00:33:03,880 --> 00:33:07,800
Yes. I'll head to the factory
first thing tomorrow morning.

480
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:14,920
As long as you can't make money
while you sleep,

481
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:16,760
you'll be working
for the rest of your life.

482
00:33:16,840 --> 00:33:20,760
That's a quote from
the most successful investor in history,

483
00:33:20,840 --> 00:33:21,680
Warren Buffett.

484
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:24,720
If you have just one expert mentor,

485
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:28,760
all of you, you, you, and you,

486
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:31,120
can become rich like me.

487
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:34,880
Everything I teach you,
I've tried it myself. It works.

488
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:37,680
I became rich. You can become rich too.

489
00:33:37,760 --> 00:33:39,000
Let's get rich together.

490
00:33:39,080 --> 00:33:40,680
-Rich!
-Rich!

491
00:33:40,760 --> 00:33:41,880
Give yourself a hand.

492
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:42,800
5G STOCK TRADING
INVEST RIGHT, GET RICH TOMORROW

493
00:33:53,320 --> 00:33:54,360
Alright.

494
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:56,040
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

495
00:33:56,120 --> 00:33:58,240
-Thanks for coming today.
-Thank you.

496
00:33:58,320 --> 00:34:01,440
Suea. This is Pound, my boyfriend.

497
00:34:01,520 --> 00:34:02,840
Hello, Suea.

498
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:05,680
I actually watch
your YouTube videos a lot.

499
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:06,760
Really happy to meet you.

500
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:07,920
Nice to meet you.

501
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:10,520
Is he the one whose family
owns a paper factory?

502
00:34:10,600 --> 00:34:14,080
Yes. In a little while,
he will take over his father's business.

503
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:19,520
Actually, I don't really want
to stay under my dad's wings.

504
00:34:20,120 --> 00:34:21,719
I'd rather invest on my own.

505
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:24,679
I like trading.
I actually trade a bit these days

506
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:26,320
just to make some pocket money,

507
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:30,800
but I want to take it seriously now.

508
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:32,320
I want to follow your method.

509
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:34,040
You made the right choice.

510
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:37,000
There are plenty of fish in the ocean.

511
00:34:37,679 --> 00:34:40,480
It's just about who sees them
and catches them first.

512
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:44,199
If you're interested in investing,

513
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:47,159
we'll arrange a meeting
to go over the details.

514
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:49,480
I'll coach you myself.

515
00:34:50,840 --> 00:34:51,840
Let's get rich together.

516
00:34:52,639 --> 00:34:54,120
Thank you so much!

517
00:34:54,199 --> 00:34:56,320
Can I take a selfie with you?

518
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:57,480
Sure, come on!

519
00:34:58,760 --> 00:35:01,480
-Selfie, please. Sorry.
-Sure, go ahead.

520
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:04,640
-My hand's a bit shaky. Sorry.
-Yeah.

521
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:08,080
<i>Cent is only giving you guys</i>
<i>five minutes each?</i>

522
00:35:09,160 --> 00:35:10,600
How many minutes did you get?

523
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:12,800
Eight.

524
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:14,800
Why do we only get five this time?

525
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:18,520
At least he's willing to listen.

526
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:23,200
What do I say in five minutes?

527
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:25,240
What do you guys want from him?

528
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:26,440
-Advice, right?
-Yeah.

529
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:30,560
If I want to start a dessert shop

530
00:35:30,640 --> 00:35:32,920
and Yuan wants to start a clothing brand,

531
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:35,080
how do we begin,
and what do we need to do?

532
00:35:35,160 --> 00:35:36,880
-Yes.
-Like how he advised Fuang.

533
00:35:36,960 --> 00:35:39,880
Actually, I can give you guys advice.

534
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:41,200
You don't even need to ask Cent.

535
00:35:41,280 --> 00:35:45,160
Then give us advice.
How am I supposed to go talk to him?

536
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:48,120
No, I don't get you guys.

537
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:50,120
I can give you advice.

538
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:52,720
But you want me to give you advice

539
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:54,760
so he can give you advice? Why?

540
00:35:54,840 --> 00:35:56,280
Wait!

541
00:35:56,360 --> 00:35:58,080
You're making it more confusing.

542
00:35:58,160 --> 00:36:00,440
So are you helping them or not?

543
00:36:00,520 --> 00:36:01,560
-Exactly!
-Exactly!

544
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:03,280
Okay.

545
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:05,880
Let's start with the basics.

546
00:36:06,680 --> 00:36:08,800
The 6 Rs and 1 H.

547
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:10,280
-Do you know that?
-Huh?

548
00:36:10,360 --> 00:36:11,240
Wait a sec.

549
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:12,200
-Hold on.
-Let me write it down.

550
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:13,240
Alright, let's start.

551
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:14,960
-Yeah, go on.
-Who.

552
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:16,960
-Who?
-Who is the customer?

553
00:36:17,040 --> 00:36:18,440
-What.
-What?

554
00:36:18,520 --> 00:36:20,080
What do they want to buy?

555
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:22,400
When. When can they buy it?

556
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:25,080
Where. Where can they buy it?

557
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:27,080
Why. Why do they need to buy it?

558
00:36:27,160 --> 00:36:30,400
Whom. Who influences the purchase?
And finally,

559
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:33,480
how. How do they buy it?

560
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:36,600
In-store, online, whatever.

561
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:40,000
It's actually not that hard.
Simple. Easy. Done!

562
00:36:41,440 --> 00:36:42,840
How is this easy?

563
00:36:43,440 --> 00:36:44,840
-Not at all.
-Did you follow that?

564
00:36:44,920 --> 00:36:46,080
Nope.

565
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:47,480
It was too fast.

566
00:36:47,560 --> 00:36:50,280
It's not easy.

567
00:36:51,280 --> 00:36:53,160
I've been thinking for a while

568
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:55,400
before deciding to sell my shares.

569
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:58,040
Then why sell it?

570
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:09,120
My life is falling apart, Cent.

571
00:37:11,800 --> 00:37:14,520
I go home and my kid won't talk to me.

572
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:19,680
She cries and won't let me hold her
because I've been gone for so long.

573
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:21,960
When I get home, she's asleep.

574
00:37:22,040 --> 00:37:25,360
When I leave for work, she's still asleep.
It's been like this for months.

575
00:37:27,200 --> 00:37:28,840
Sometimes I feel like…

576
00:37:30,640 --> 00:37:32,360
I'm losing her.

577
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:36,560
You're not a father.

578
00:37:36,640 --> 00:37:40,200
You wouldn't understand
how painful this is.

579
00:37:43,040 --> 00:37:44,360
Even if you were a father,

580
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:46,960
maybe you still wouldn't understand.

581
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:52,520
You're going too far, Ken.
I do have feelings too!

582
00:37:56,160 --> 00:37:59,320
At least I know
you don't want me to lose this company.

583
00:38:02,040 --> 00:38:05,160
I know you love this company, Cent.

584
00:38:05,240 --> 00:38:07,240
It's like your whole life.

585
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:11,160
But get this.

586
00:38:11,800 --> 00:38:12,640
What?

587
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:16,400
The VC doesn't just want the company.

588
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:20,480
They want you out too.

589
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:26,720
Kick me out?

590
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:29,200
They're going to remove me?

591
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:32,440
If they hold the majority of shares,

592
00:38:33,240 --> 00:38:35,200
they'll remove you
from your executive position.

593
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:39,080
Why?

594
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:44,560
They say you don't get along with people.

595
00:38:46,840 --> 00:38:49,960
You're hard to work with.
You have communication problems.

596
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:51,480
Do you know that?

597
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:57,640
Just because of that?

598
00:38:58,320 --> 00:38:59,240
Really?

599
00:38:59,320 --> 00:39:02,200
Just because I don't like small talk
or chatting with employees,

600
00:39:02,720 --> 00:39:03,560
they're going to…

601
00:39:04,960 --> 00:39:06,440
remove me from the company?

602
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:08,680
Is it really that easy, Ken?

603
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:12,840
All those seven years, I built the system,
wrote the code, fixed bugs,

604
00:39:12,920 --> 00:39:14,800
solved impossible problems,

605
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:17,920
none of that matters? Answer me!

606
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:21,200
It does matter, Cent.

607
00:39:22,440 --> 00:39:24,480
But money makes it simple.

608
00:39:28,040 --> 00:39:31,040
They have the money.
If they buy enough shares in our company,

609
00:39:31,120 --> 00:39:32,960
they can push us out.

610
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:35,880
That's all there is to it, Cent.

611
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:41,600
<i>Honestly, there's nothing</i>
<i>that hard about it.</i>

612
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:43,960
Lots of people start their own companies.

613
00:39:44,760 --> 00:39:47,600
Just go for it! Trust me! Do it!

614
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:51,440
I'll be your advisor.
No need to rely on Cent.

615
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:55,160
Fuang already set up
a meeting with her boss.

616
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:57,680
If you guys don't go, she will look bad.

617
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:59,400
Yeah, that's true.

618
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:02,800
Okay then.

619
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:05,400
I'll think about what you said

620
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:09,280
and talk to Cent later.
Maybe he'll have more advice.

621
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:11,840
Yeah. It doesn't hurt to try!

622
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:14,920
If I can do it, you guys can too!
Let's go!

623
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:17,240
-Let's go!
-Let's do this!

624
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:18,800
Yeah.

625
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:22,960
If Bonus and Yuan's ideas are really good,

626
00:40:23,040 --> 00:40:25,520
do you think Cent would invest in them
like he did for you?

627
00:40:26,680 --> 00:40:27,840
Well…

628
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:31,960
If he doesn't want to invest,

629
00:40:33,520 --> 00:40:35,160
-I will!
-What?

630
00:40:38,240 --> 00:40:39,680
I told you already.

631
00:40:40,200 --> 00:40:44,160
Starting your own business isn't hard.
It's super easy, I'm telling you!

632
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:48,440
Alright.

633
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:50,840
We'll get rich together!

634
00:40:52,280 --> 00:40:53,800
Rich! Rich! Rich!

635
00:40:53,880 --> 00:40:55,080
-Come on!
-We'll get rich!

636
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:58,480
Rich! Rich! Rich!

637
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:00,760
<i>I used to think</i>
<i>starting a company was easy.</i>

638
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:03,880
Just get money from Mom
and we could do it.

639
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:07,160
But in reality, it's so much harder.

640
00:41:07,920 --> 00:41:10,640
We still made it work. Look around you!

641
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:11,960
But we're exhausted, Cent!

642
00:41:12,040 --> 00:41:13,600
But we got everything we wanted,
didn't we?

643
00:41:13,680 --> 00:41:15,360
What about everything we lost?

644
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:18,960
You're so obsessed with work
that you have no one left.

645
00:41:19,040 --> 00:41:22,720
Think about it.
If you didn't have me today,

646
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:25,200
who would you even have left in your life?

647
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:42,320
I can't lose this company.

648
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:45,080
I built it, so I'll do whatever it takes
to protect it.

649
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:49,000
As for the shares, don't sell them yet.

650
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:52,680
Wait until I secure my mom's shares.
Then you can sell. I won't stop you.

651
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:54,920
But for now, please, Ken,

652
00:41:55,680 --> 00:41:56,920
hold on to them.

653
00:41:58,560 --> 00:41:59,560
Please.

654
00:42:06,560 --> 00:42:07,480
Yeah.

655
00:42:12,720 --> 00:42:17,120
Give me a few more months.
I'll get everything sorted out quickly.

656
00:42:27,040 --> 00:42:29,480
Now I get it.
It's not hard to start something.

657
00:42:35,400 --> 00:42:38,760
But it's damn hard to keep it going.

658
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:59,240
Thanks for the ride, miss.
I'm off now. Bye!

659
00:42:59,320 --> 00:43:00,240
Okay.

660
00:43:00,760 --> 00:43:02,720
Hey, wait. I've got something to ask you.

661
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:07,360
You said Cent is really smart

662
00:43:07,440 --> 00:43:09,000
and gave you good advice.

663
00:43:09,840 --> 00:43:13,560
If I want him to advise me about work,
do you think he'd talk to me?

664
00:43:18,680 --> 00:43:20,360
Do you already have a job you want to do?

665
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:40,800
Mom.

666
00:43:40,880 --> 00:43:43,280
Are you really not going
to let me stay with you?

667
00:43:43,360 --> 00:43:45,760
Just take me to the hospital.

668
00:43:45,840 --> 00:43:48,840
Once I get there,
the nurses will take good care of me.

669
00:43:50,240 --> 00:43:51,960
You stay and watch the shop.

670
00:43:53,360 --> 00:43:54,840
Keep an eye on Cent.

671
00:44:04,160 --> 00:44:05,360
They say

672
00:44:05,440 --> 00:44:09,440
stress feeds cancer, Mom.

673
00:44:09,520 --> 00:44:12,720
So don't stress, okay?

674
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:13,840
I know that!

675
00:44:13,920 --> 00:44:16,080
-Mom, is there anything to eat?
-Oh no!

676
00:44:16,160 --> 00:44:17,960
Quick, hide it!

677
00:44:18,040 --> 00:44:20,400
-He can still see it.
-No!

678
00:44:21,280 --> 00:44:22,800
-Hurry up!
-Alright, sit down.

679
00:44:22,880 --> 00:44:24,320
He's here!

680
00:44:29,640 --> 00:44:32,200
Cent, come here! Hurry up.

681
00:44:37,360 --> 00:44:38,840
You look so serious reading.

682
00:44:39,560 --> 00:44:40,360
Like you're taking an exam.

683
00:44:42,760 --> 00:44:44,400
Kind of! Because…

684
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:47,120
Mom is planning a trip soon.

685
00:44:47,200 --> 00:44:48,960
-Yeah.
-I got her some books to read

686
00:44:49,040 --> 00:44:51,240
for her information
so she can enjoy her trip more.

687
00:44:51,320 --> 00:44:53,680
Yes, I'm planning
a short break for a few days.

688
00:44:53,760 --> 00:44:55,800
I've already decided where I'm going.

689
00:44:55,880 --> 00:44:57,360
I've got some ideas in mind.

690
00:44:57,440 --> 00:44:58,480
Which province are you going to?

691
00:44:58,560 --> 00:45:00,000
-Chiang Rai!
-Phuket!

692
00:45:02,920 --> 00:45:03,880
So which one is it?

693
00:45:06,760 --> 00:45:08,000
Pong!

694
00:45:08,520 --> 00:45:09,720
I said I'm going north

695
00:45:09,800 --> 00:45:12,480
to pray at temples,
not go south to Phuket!

696
00:45:12,560 --> 00:45:14,520
Are you sending me
scuba diving or something?

697
00:45:14,600 --> 00:45:15,840
Sorry, I got it wrong.

698
00:45:15,920 --> 00:45:17,440
Chiang Rai it is.

699
00:45:17,520 --> 00:45:18,880
You said you were hungry, right?

700
00:45:18,960 --> 00:45:22,080
I've got plenty of food today!
What do you want to eat?

701
00:45:23,120 --> 00:45:24,320
Pong, go to the kitchen.

702
00:45:25,120 --> 00:45:26,800
-Yes, ma'am.
-Let's go!

703
00:45:26,880 --> 00:45:28,760
-Oh.
-Let's go.

704
00:45:28,840 --> 00:45:30,640
-Everything's delicious.
-What do you have?

705
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:46,960
What's wrong?

706
00:45:47,840 --> 00:45:49,560
Did you not sort things out with Kenji?

707
00:45:53,560 --> 00:45:55,640
Mom, don't stress.

708
00:45:55,720 --> 00:45:59,040
Stay calm. Take a deep breath.

709
00:46:00,160 --> 00:46:01,440
Pong.

710
00:46:02,400 --> 00:46:04,640
I'm the one who's stressed here, not Mom.

711
00:46:05,440 --> 00:46:06,680
You should be comforting me.

712
00:46:07,200 --> 00:46:08,720
Oh, right.

713
00:46:08,800 --> 00:46:12,560
Right. Cent, don't stress, okay?

714
00:46:12,640 --> 00:46:16,000
By the way, what are you stressed about?

715
00:46:18,960 --> 00:46:20,160
Kenji said

716
00:46:20,240 --> 00:46:23,440
if the investors
get a majority stake in the company,

717
00:46:24,200 --> 00:46:26,120
they'll remove me
from my executive position.

718
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:27,400
-What?
-Huh?

719
00:46:28,680 --> 00:46:30,320
Do they really have to go that far?

720
00:46:30,840 --> 00:46:33,280
Are you having problems with someone?
When did that happen?

721
00:46:33,360 --> 00:46:35,560
I'm not having problems with anyone, Mom.

722
00:46:41,560 --> 00:46:43,240
I'm just having problems with myself.

723
00:46:43,320 --> 00:46:44,320
-Huh?
-Huh?

724
00:46:46,600 --> 00:46:48,800
-They said I--
-You can't work with your team.

725
00:46:50,280 --> 00:46:51,720
You don't communicate properly.

726
00:46:52,880 --> 00:46:54,960
You don't talk to anyone at work.

727
00:46:55,040 --> 00:46:58,760
Without Kenji, no one can work with you.

728
00:46:58,840 --> 00:47:00,840
Did Kenji call you?

729
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:03,160
I'm your mother.
I don't need anyone to tell me.

730
00:47:03,760 --> 00:47:04,920
I already know.

731
00:47:07,200 --> 00:47:08,240
Cent.

732
00:47:09,560 --> 00:47:12,680
I know you don't like repeating things.

733
00:47:13,960 --> 00:47:17,320
But you need to learn
to listen and trust me.

734
00:47:19,080 --> 00:47:22,560
Don't think Kenji will always be there
to hold everything together.

735
00:47:23,160 --> 00:47:25,560
One day, he'll have his own life.

736
00:47:29,000 --> 00:47:30,680
And even I…

737
00:47:31,760 --> 00:47:33,880
One day, I'll have my own life too.

738
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:36,480
You need to find friends,

739
00:47:36,560 --> 00:47:39,720
a social life,
someone to be there for you.

740
00:47:39,800 --> 00:47:42,200
People you feel comfortable with.

741
00:47:43,120 --> 00:47:47,240
Cent. If you don't learn
to keep an open mind,

742
00:47:48,360 --> 00:47:52,600
someday you might end up
with nothing left.

743
00:47:53,920 --> 00:47:58,120
Both your friends and the company
you built with your own hands.

744
00:48:49,400 --> 00:48:53,000
<i>No plates? Alright, hold on!</i>

745
00:49:36,920 --> 00:49:37,960
<i>Cent!</i>

746
00:49:38,040 --> 00:49:40,880
-I have something for you.
-What is it?

747
00:49:43,120 --> 00:49:44,880
If you want to know, just open it.

748
00:50:06,880 --> 00:50:09,680
FUANG SENT YOU A VOICE MESSAGE

749
00:50:09,760 --> 00:50:11,000
Speak of the devil.

750
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:16,880
FUANG

751
00:50:16,960 --> 00:50:18,560
<i>Hello, Cent.</i>

752
00:50:20,760 --> 00:50:22,240
Welcome home.

753
00:50:25,480 --> 00:50:29,760
I have something I want to ask you
before we meet tomorrow.

754
00:50:29,840 --> 00:50:31,480
Well…

755
00:50:40,560 --> 00:50:41,480
What is it?

756
00:50:48,040 --> 00:50:49,080
FUANG

757
00:50:49,160 --> 00:50:50,480
<i>I…</i>

758
00:50:50,560 --> 00:50:53,800
I have another friend
who wants to ask for your advice too.

759
00:50:53,880 --> 00:50:55,560
Now there'll be three instead of two.

760
00:50:56,160 --> 00:50:58,520
<i>It'll take fifteen minutes instead of ten.</i>

761
00:50:59,040 --> 00:51:02,080
Would that be okay?

762
00:51:02,680 --> 00:51:04,320
Please!

763
00:51:18,560 --> 00:51:20,040
<i>You need to learn to have friends,</i>

764
00:51:20,120 --> 00:51:23,560
<i>a social life. If you don't learn</i>
<i>to keep an open mind,</i>

765
00:51:23,640 --> 00:51:27,760
<i>someday you might end up</i>
<i>with nothing left, both your friends</i>

766
00:51:27,840 --> 00:51:29,760
<i>and the company</i>
<i>you built with your own hands.</i>

767
00:51:58,000 --> 00:51:59,080
<i>Okay.</i>

768
00:52:03,880 --> 00:52:04,880
Thank you so much!

769
00:52:04,960 --> 00:52:08,000
Where should me and my friends
meet you tomorrow?

770
00:52:37,320 --> 00:52:39,760
Cent's office is really grand!

771
00:52:39,840 --> 00:52:42,000
He must be really rich.

772
00:52:42,080 --> 00:52:45,240
No, super rich!

773
00:52:47,960 --> 00:52:49,280
Fuang, you're so lucky.

774
00:52:50,440 --> 00:52:52,040
You get to work in such a fancy office.

775
00:52:54,040 --> 00:52:55,040
Let's go!

776
00:52:58,400 --> 00:52:59,400
Let's go.

777
00:53:02,680 --> 00:53:03,520
Wait!

778
00:53:05,280 --> 00:53:09,040
I thought you were just coming along,
but Fuang said you're also presenting?

779
00:53:11,040 --> 00:53:14,360
It's not just you and Yuan
who have dreams. I do too.

780
00:53:15,280 --> 00:53:16,120
What job is it?

781
00:53:17,040 --> 00:53:18,080
You'll see.

782
00:53:31,120 --> 00:53:32,480
Excuse me. Coming through.

783
00:53:32,560 --> 00:53:34,200
-Whoa!
-Watch out!

784
00:53:36,440 --> 00:53:38,440
-Is that allowed in the office?
-Right.

785
00:53:39,640 --> 00:53:41,200
-That's cool.
-Can you really do that?

786
00:53:50,720 --> 00:53:52,200
This place is huge.

787
00:53:52,280 --> 00:53:54,040
Where is it?

788
00:53:54,120 --> 00:53:56,200
Where's Cent's office?

789
00:53:56,280 --> 00:53:58,240
He said it's somewhere around here.

790
00:53:58,320 --> 00:54:00,520
Call him and ask.
Maybe he's already waiting for us.

791
00:54:00,600 --> 00:54:01,440
Okay, one sec.

792
00:54:05,040 --> 00:54:06,280
I'm here.

793
00:54:08,200 --> 00:54:09,400
Hello, Cent.

794
00:54:09,480 --> 00:54:10,400
-Hello.
-Hello.

795
00:54:10,480 --> 00:54:11,520
Hello.

796
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:13,160
This way.

797
00:54:21,320 --> 00:54:22,520
Let's head inside!

798
00:54:33,040 --> 00:54:35,960
Is this your workspace, Cent?

799
00:54:36,040 --> 00:54:37,560
No, this is the office.

800
00:54:37,640 --> 00:54:40,440
Your office?

801
00:54:43,720 --> 00:54:46,440
Yeah, this is the whole office.

802
00:54:52,320 --> 00:54:53,600
Who's first?

803
00:54:54,600 --> 00:54:55,440
I'll go first.

804
00:54:56,040 --> 00:54:58,080
Go ahead. The rest of you wait outside.

805
00:55:02,840 --> 00:55:04,960
Let's wait outside.

806
00:55:15,880 --> 00:55:19,080
He doesn't need to be that harsh.
He could've just spoken nicely.

807
00:55:20,080 --> 00:55:23,520
You're getting his advice for free.
If you don't like it, just leave.

808
00:55:23,600 --> 00:55:25,000
I never said that.

809
00:55:26,080 --> 00:55:28,600
Hey, stop fighting.

810
00:55:29,520 --> 00:55:32,040
Who's next? Get ready.

811
00:55:32,920 --> 00:55:33,840
I'll go.

812
00:55:40,400 --> 00:55:43,280
I'm telling you, it's pointless.

813
00:55:44,560 --> 00:55:47,920
From the way he looks,
he won't be able to help you guys.

814
00:56:11,200 --> 00:56:13,080
I'm going to become an influencer.

815
00:56:13,160 --> 00:56:14,880
What is an influencer?

816
00:56:14,960 --> 00:56:16,880
How is it different
from a content creator?

817
00:56:16,960 --> 00:56:18,800
What are KOLs and KOCs?

818
00:56:18,880 --> 00:56:21,280
Mega, macro, micro, nano,
how do you measure them?

819
00:56:23,080 --> 00:56:28,200
I know how painful it is when your parents
look down on you and don't believe in you.

820
00:56:32,240 --> 00:56:33,960
Let's fight together.

821
00:56:34,040 --> 00:56:37,240
Don't take another cent from this old man!

822
00:56:37,840 --> 00:56:40,960
And don't you ever think

823
00:56:41,040 --> 00:56:42,840
you're the only one

824
00:56:43,960 --> 00:56:46,040
who's suffering because you're my son.

825
00:56:47,960 --> 00:56:50,680
Thank you so much! Thank you.

826
00:56:59,320 --> 00:57:00,560
Thank you so much!

827
00:57:43,200 --> 00:57:48,280
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
